<div>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><strong>Example 1:</strong>&nbsp;The floor o=
f a&nbsp;whispering gallery is constructed in the shape of an ellipse. Find=
&nbsp;area of ellipse, if the length of its major axis is 14 units&nbsp;and=
 the length of its minor axis is 10&nbsp;units.</p>
<p data-speechify-sentence=3D"" style=3D"text-align: left;"><strong>Solutio=
n:</strong></p>
<p data-speechify-sentence=3D"" style=3D"text-align: left;">Given that,<br>
	Length of major axis =3D 14 units<br>
	=E2=87=92&nbsp;length of semi-major axis is =3D&nbsp;(1/2)&nbsp;=C3=97 14 =
=3D 7 units.<br>
	Length of minor axis =3D 10 units<br>
	=E2=87=92&nbsp;length of semi-minor axis is =3D&nbsp;(1/2)&nbsp;=C3=97 10&=
